# Orlovka, Yanaulsky District, Republic of Bashkortostan

}}
Orlovka () is a rural locality (a selo) and the administrative centre of Orlovsky Selsoviet, Yanaulsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 374 as of 2010. There are 3 streets.
Geography
Orlovka is located 26&nbsp;km southeast of Yanaul (the district's administrative centre) by road. Yamyady is the nearest rural locality.
